'''Fredrik André Bjørkan''' (born 21 August 1998) is a Norwegian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Eliteserien]] club [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Carlsson|first=Alexander|date=1 December 2021|title=Fredrik André Björkan ansluter i Januari|trans-title=Fredrik André Björkan joins in January|url=https://www.svenskafans.com/tyskland/fredrik-andre-bjorkan-ansluer-i-januari-637870|access-date=1 December 2021|website=SvenskaFans.com|language=sv}}</ref>

== Club career ==

=== Bodø/Glimt ===
Bjørkan was born in [[Bodø (town)|Bodø]], [[Nordland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=298869&tournamentId=1&seasonId=338&teamId=307&useFullUrl=false |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601111049/http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=298869&tournamentId=1&seasonId=338&teamId=307&useFullUrl=false |url-status=dead |archive-date=1 June 2016 |title=Fredrik André Bjørkan |work=altomfotball.no |publisher=TV2 |accessdate=1 May 2016}}</ref> He started playing for hometown club [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] as a youth and made his first professional appearance at age 17, on 13 April 2016, in the [[Norwegian Football Cup]], against [[IF Fløya]], which Bodø/Glimt won 6&ndash;0.{{Citation needed|date=December 2021}} He made his league debut for Bodø/Glimt on 17 April 2016 against [[Molde FK|Molde]] where Bodø/Glimt lost 2–1.{{Citation needed|date=December 2021}}

=== Hertha BSC ===
On 1 December 2021, Bjørkan signed for [[Hertha BSC]] on a contract until 2025,<ref>{{Cite web|date=1 December 2021|title=Fredrik Andre Björkan wechselt zu Hertha BSC|trans-title=Fredrik Andre Björkan moves to Hertha BSC|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/hertha-bsc-fredrik-andre-bjorkan-transfer-wechsel-fk-bodo-glimt-18064|access-date=1 December 2021|publisher=[[Bundesliga]]|language=de}}</ref> joining at the beginning of the January [[transfer window]].<ref name=":0" /> Bjørkan moved back to Bodø/Glimt in January 2023.<ref name="return">{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-neemt-na-half-jaar-al-afscheid-van-bjorkan |title=Feyenoord neemt na half jaar al afscheid van Bjørkan |trans-title=Feyenoors says goodbye to Bjørkan after 6 months |date=4 January 2022 |access-date=4 January 2022}}</ref>

==== Feyenoord (loan) ====
On 29 August 2022, [[Feyenoord]] announced that it had signed Bjørkan on loan with an option to buy.<ref name="vi_feyenoor">{{cite web |url=https://www.vi.nl/nieuws/feyenoord-heeft-met-bjorkan-veertiende-zomeraanwinst-binnen |title=Feyenoord heeft met Bjørkan veertiende zomeraanwinst binnen |trans-title=With Bjørkan Feyenoord brings in fourteenth summer signing |language=Dutch |date=29 August 2022 |access-date=29 August 2022}}</ref> The loan agreement was disbanded in January 2023.<ref name="return"/>

==International career==
Bjørkan made his debut for the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]] on 6 June 2021 in a [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] against [[Greece national football team|Greece]]. He substituted [[Birger Meling]] in the 69th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=600641|title=Norway v Greece game report|date=6 June 2021}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Fredrik André is the son of former player [[Aasmund Bjørkan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ansatte|url=https://www.glimt.no/om-klubben/ansatte|work=glimt.no|publisher=Bodø/Glimt|accessdate=30 August 2019}}</ref>

